# coreboot config fragment — QEMU q35 + LinuxBoot payload, tuned for NETWORK boot
# (u-root `pxeboot`). This is the PLAN-PXEBOOT P1 sibling of
# coreboot-qemu-q35-linuxboot.config; build it with:
#
#   ./fetch-go.sh                                  # Go 1.25 (u-root main needs it)
#   CBCONFIG=coreboot-qemu-q35-pxeboot.config \
#     UROOT_GOBIN="$HOME/linuxboot-lab/go1.25/bin" ./build-coreboot.sh
#
# Two deliberate differences from the disk-finale config, both forced by a fully
# diagnosed finding (see POC-PXEBOOT.md):
#
#  1. **u-root MAIN, not v0.14.0.** We still can't use u-root's DHCP (its AF_PACKET
#     client emits zero packets over QEMU slirp — true on v0.14.0 AND main). But
#     main's `pxeboot -file <URI>` takes a "manual target" that SKIPS DHCP and
#     fetches over an already-configured interface. main needs Go >= 1.25.
#  2. **`ip=dhcp` on the kernel cmdline.** The Linux *kernel's* in-stack DHCP
#     (CONFIG_IP_PNP_DHCP) works fine over slirp, so the kernel brings the NIC up
#     with a real lease before u-root runs; then `pxeboot -file` uses it. The payload
#     kernel also gets NIC drivers + virtio-rng via build-coreboot.sh's §3a block
#     (u-root netboot needs entropy, and QEMU needs `-device virtio-rng-pci`).
#
# SPECIFIC_BOOTLOADER is left NONE so u-root drops to a shell and `pxeboot -file …`
# is TYPED (drive-boot.py) — a uinit symlink can't carry the `-file` flag. The
# verified transcript (AlmaLinux 9.8 Anaconda auto-installing) is in POC-PXEBOOT.md.

CONFIG_BOARD_EMULATION_QEMU_X86_Q35=y
CONFIG_COREBOOT_ROMSIZE_KB_16384=y          # 16 MB ROM

CONFIG_PAYLOAD_LINUXBOOT=y
CONFIG_LINUXBOOT_X86_64=y
CONFIG_LINUXBOOT_COMPILE_KERNEL=y
CONFIG_LINUXBOOT_KERNEL_VERSION="6.3"
CONFIG_LINUX_COMMAND_LINE="console=ttyS0 ip=dhcp"   # kernel does the DHCP (slirp-friendly)

CONFIG_LINUXBOOT_BUILD_INITRAMFS=y
CONFIG_LINUXBOOT_UROOT=y
CONFIG_LINUXBOOT_UROOT_MAIN=y               # u-root main → `pxeboot -file` (needs Go 1.25)
# pxeboot is in-module; the full import path is required (a bare `pxeboot` is read by
# `go list` as a stdlib import and fails — see POC-PXEBOOT.md). kexec (core) is added
# for the P2 HTTPS tier: u-root's `pxeboot` has NO https scheme (DefaultSchemes =
# tftp/http/file only), but its `wget` does (Go SystemCertPool). So P2 fetches the
# kernel+initrd with `wget https://…` (trusting the baked lab CA below) and boots them
# with the `kexec` command — no patched payload. `pxeboot -file http://…` (P1) is
# unchanged; one ROM carries both tiers.
CONFIG_LINUXBOOT_UROOT_COMMANDS="boot coreboot-app github.com/u-root/u-root/cmds/boot/pxeboot github.com/u-root/u-root/cmds/core/kexec"
# P2: bake the shared lab CA into the initramfs at Go's SystemCertPool path so u-root's
# wget trusts https://… served by a lab-CA cert. build-coreboot.sh stages lab-ca.crt
# (public cert only) from examples/lab-ca/ next to the tree; the Makefile places it.
CONFIG_LINUXBOOT_UROOT_FILES="lab-ca.crt:/etc/ssl/certs/ca-certificates.crt"
CONFIG_SPECIFIC_BOOTLOADER_NONE=y           # drop to shell; the fetch+boot cmds are typed
